name: Customer Action Responded
type: Coordination/Response
description: |
  Response event returned after a customer-facing provider handled a Customer Action Requested event. It records which
  action label the customer chose, any input collected from the user, and when the provider says the response occurred.

  `actionLabel` should correspond to one of the requested action labels. `input` carries optional structured user input.
  `respondedAt` records provider-supplied response time. The response should be correlated to the original request using
  the inherited Response correlation fields when available.

  This event is evidence that the provider obtained a customer decision. It does not by itself prove that the action is
  authorized under every document policy; workflows may still inspect actor, source, input, and response details before
  applying state changes.
actionLabel:
  type: Text
  description: Label of the action selected by the user.
input:
  description: Optional user-provided payload for the selected action.
respondedAt:
  type: Common/Timestamp
  description: Timestamp when the user decision was recorded by the bank.
